# No Markdown Files Rule

## NEVER Create These Files Anywhere:

❌ README.md
❌ QUICK_START.md  
❌ GUIDE.md
❌ ARCHITECTURE.md
❌ MIGRATION.md
❌ INSTRUCTIONS.md
❌ Any other .md files in root or subdirectories

## Exception: Documentation Folder Only

✅ `documentation/` - ONLY place for .md files
✅ `documentation/components/` - Component docs
✅ `documentation/instructions/` - Usage instructions

## If You Need to Document Something:

### Component Documentation:
- Add to: `documentation/components/[ComponentName].md`
- Example: `documentation/components/MapLibrary.md`

### Usage Instructions:
- Update: `documentation/instructions/how-to-use.md`
- Don't create new files, update existing ones

### Project Changes:
- Update: `documentation/PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md`
- Or update: `documentation/index.md`

## Why This Rule?

- Prevents documentation clutter
- Keeps project clean
- Single source of truth in `documentation/`
- Easier to find information
- Professional project structure

## Remember:

**NO .md files outside `documentation/` folder - EVER!**
